  "source": "Theorem:\n. \"Theorem 4.36 (Well Ordering Principle)\"\ngiven:\n. X is \\set\nthen:\n. \\well.ordered{X}\nDocumented:\n. description: \"Assuming the axioms of ZF and Zorn's lemma, every set can be well ordered. One applies Zorn's lemma to the collection of well orderings of subsets of $X$, ordered by continuation; a maximal element must well order all of $X$.\"\nId: \"8671e667-d056-44e4-a56a-e0fc963f753f\"",
